{"action": "input", "code": "def get_pixel_color(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    return input_grid[1][1]\ndef paint_black_squares_orange(input_grid: np.ndarray, corners: Tuple[Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int]]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Paint all black squares on the line from upper left to lower right in orange, and paint all black squares on the line from lower left to upper right in orange.\n    \"\"\"\n    n = count_colors(input_grid)\n    big_grid = enlarge_image(input_grid)\n    (x1, y1), (x2, y2), (x3, y3), (x4, y4) = corners\n    for i in range(x1, x4 + 1):\n        if big_grid[i][i] == black:\n            big_grid[i][i] = orange\n    for i in range(x3, x2 - 1, -1):\n        if big_grid[i][10 * n - i] == black:\n            big_grid[i][10 * n - i] = orange\n    return big_grid\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    n = count_colors(input_grid)\n    c = get_pixel_color(input_grid)\n    big_grid = enlarge_image(input_grid)\n    corners = find_corners(big_grid)\n    output_grid = paint_black_squares_orange(big_grid, corners)\n    return output_grid\ndef enlarge_image(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    n = count_colors(input_grid)\n    return np.kron(input_grid, np.ones((5 * n, 5 * n)))\ndef find_corners(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Find out the coordinates of the four corners of the square on the enlarged image, denoted as (x1,y1), (x2,y2), (x3,y3), and (x4,y4) (respectively, upper left, upper right, lower left, and lower right).\n    \"\"\"\n    n = count_colors(input_grid)\n    x1, y1 = (2 * n, 2 * n)\n    x2, y2 = (2 * n, 10 * n)\n    x3, y3 = (10 * n, 2 * n)\n    x4, y4 = (10 * n, 10 * n)\n    return ((x1, y1), (x2, y2), (x3, y3), (x4, y4))\ndef count_colors(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    unique_colors = set(np.unique(input_grid))\n    if black in unique_colors:\n        unique_colors.remove(black)\n    return len(unique_colors)", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    # Task description: The input is a black background image matrix with a size of 5*5. There is a solid square and an L-shaped figure (along the lower edge and right edge of the image) in the picture. What you need to do is: (1) Find out how many colors there are in the image, and the number of colors is n (excluding the black background color); (2) Find out the color c of the square; (3) Enlarge the original image proportionally to 5n*5n; (4) Find out the coordinates of the four corners of the square on the enlarged image, denoted as (x1,y1), (x2,y2), (x3,y3), and (x4,y4) (respectively, upper left, upper right, lower left, and lower right); (5) Paint all black squares on the line from upper left to lower right in orange, and paint all black squares on the line from lower left to upper right in orange.\n    n = `Find out how many colors there are in the image(excluding the black background color).`(input_grid)\n    c = `Find the color of the pixel at coordinate (1,1) in the image (coordinates start from 0).`(input_grid)\n    big_grid = `Enlarge the original image proportionally to 5n*5n`(input_grid)\n    corners = `Find out the coordinates of the four corners of the square on the enlarged image, denoted as (x1,y1), (x2,y2), (x3,y3), and (x4,y4) (respectively, upper left, upper right, lower left, and lower right).`(big_grid)\n    output_grid = `Paint all black squares on the line from upper left to lower right in orange, and paint all black squares on the line from lower left to upper right in orange.`(big_grid, corners)\n    return output_grid\n    ", "gpt_code": "def get_pixel_color(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    return input_grid[1][1]\ndef paint_black_squares_orange(input_grid: np.ndarray, corners: Tuple[Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int]]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Paint all black squares on the line from upper left to lower right in orange, and paint all black squares on the line from lower left to upper right in orange.\n    \"\"\"\n    n = count_colors(input_grid)\n    big_grid = enlarge_image(input_grid)\n    (x1, y1), (x2, y2), (x3, y3), (x4, y4) = corners\n    for i in range(x1, x4 + 1):\n        if big_grid[i][i] == black:\n            big_grid[i][i] = orange\n    for i in range(x3, x2 - 1, -1):\n        if big_grid[i][10 * n - i] == black:\n            big_grid[i][10 * n - i] = orange\n    return big_grid\ndef enlarge_image(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    n = count_colors(input_grid)\n    return np.kron(input_grid, np.ones((5 * n, 5 * n)))\ndef find_corners(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Find out the coordinates of the four corners of the square on the enlarged image, denoted as (x1,y1), (x2,y2), (x3,y3), and (x4,y4) (respectively, upper left, upper right, lower left, and lower right).\n    \"\"\"\n    n = count_colors(input_grid)\n    x1, y1 = (2 * n, 2 * n)\n    x2, y2 = (2 * n, 10 * n)\n    x3, y3 = (10 * n, 2 * n)\n    x4, y4 = (10 * n, 10 * n)\n    return ((x1, y1), (x2, y2), (x3, y3), (x4, y4))\ndef count_colors(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    unique_colors = set(np.unique(input_grid))\n    if black in unique_colors:\n        unique_colors.remove(black)\n    return len(unique_colors)", "holes": {"get_pixel_color": "Find the color of the pixel at coordinate (1,1) in the image (coordinates start from 0).", "paint_black_squares_orange": "Paint all black squares on the line from upper left to lower right in orange, and paint all black squares on the line from lower left to upper right in orange.", "enlarge_image": "Enlarge the original image proportionally to 5n*5n", "find_corners": "Find out the coordinates of the four corners of the square on the enlarged image, denoted as (x1,y1), (x2,y2), (x3,y3), and (x4,y4) (respectively, upper left, upper right, lower left, an